'''Amar Dedić''' ({{IPA|bs|ǎmar dêːditɕ|pron}}; born 18 August 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]. Born in Austria, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Dedić started his professional career at [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]], who assigned him to [[FC Liefering|Liefering]] in 2019 and loaned him to [[Wolfsberger AC]] in 2021 and to [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in 2025. Later that year, he signed with Benfica.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Dedić made his senior international debut in 2022, earning over 20 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Red Bull Salzburg===
Dedić started playing football at a local club, before joining [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz's youth setup]] in 2012. In 2015, he moved to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg's youth academy]]. In August 2019, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/mladi-bh-reprezentativac-potpisao-za-salzburg/20415|title=Mladi bh. reprezentativac potpisao za Salzburg|website=faktor.ba|date=1 August 2019|access-date=1 August 2019|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut playing for Red Bull Salzburg's [[Farm team#Association football|feeder squad]], [[FC Liefering|Liefering]], against [[SKU Amstetten|Amstetten]] on 26 July at the age of 16.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/281198-amar-dedic-sa-16-godina-debitovao-u-seniorskom-fudbalu|title=Amar Dedić sa 16 godina debitovao u seniorskom fudbalu|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=26 July 2019|access-date=28 July 2019|language=bs}}</ref> On 19 June 2020, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FC Dornbirn 1913|Dornbirn]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/302551-amar-dedic-je-sa-17-godina-zabio-svoj-prvi-gol-u-seniorskoj-karijeri|title=Amar Dedić je sa 17 godina zabio svoj prvi gol u seniorskoj karijeri|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=19 June 2020|access-date=20 June 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In July, Dedić signed a new four-year deal with Red Bull Salzburg.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/amar-dedic-u-salzburgu-do-ljeta-2024-godine/368862|title=Amar Dedić u Salzburgu do ljeta 2024. godine|website=sportsport.ba|date=17 July 2020|access-date=17 July 2020|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the club in an [[2020–21 Austrian Cup#First round|Austrian Cup]] game against [[Schwarz-Weiß Bregenz|Bregenz]] on 9 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/594174/nas-talentovani-reprezentativac-debitovao-za-salzburg|title=Naš talentovani reprezentativac debitovao za Salzburg|website=avaz.ba|date=10 September 2020|access-date=13 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2021, he was sent on a season-long loan to [[Wolfsberger AC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://raport.ba/misimovic-ga-ne-hvali-slucajno-velika-nada-bh-reprezentacije-potpisala-za-novi-klub|title=Misimović ga ne hvali slučajno: Velika nada bh. reprezentacije potpisala za novi klub|website=raport.ba|date=18 June 2021|access-date=18 June 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

Dedić made his league debut for Red Bull Salzburg on 6 August 2022 against [[TSV Hartberg|Hartberg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/dedic-za-mlade-igrace-poput-mene-salzburg-je-idealan-klub-za-razvoj-zelim-se-dokazati/131685|title=Dedić: Za mlade igrače poput mene Salzburg je idealan klub za razvoj, želim se dokazati|website=faktor.ba|date=7 August 2022|access-date=8 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League#Group E|UEFA Champions League]] against [[AC Milan|Milan]] on 6 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/369623-dedic-nakon-debija-u-ligi-sampiona-ovo-je-velika-stvar-za-mene|title=Dedić nakon debija u Ligi šampiona: Ovo je velika stvar za mene|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=7 September 2022|access-date=8 September 2022|language=bs}}</ref> On 19 October, he scored his first goal for the side in an [[2022–23 Austrian Cup#First round|Austrian Cup]] match against [[Admira Wacker]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/amar-dedic-postigao-prvi-pogodak-u-karijeri-za-red-bull-salzburg-802272|title=Amar Dedić postigao prvi pogodak u karijeri za Red Bull Salzburg|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=20 October 2022|access-date=23 October 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2023, he extended his contract with the team until June 2027.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/amar-dedic-produzio-ugovor-sa-salzburgom-do-ljeta-2027-godine/230111085|title=Amar Dedić produžio ugovor sa Salzburgom do ljeta 2027. godine|website=klix.ba|date=11 January 2023|access-date=13 January 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

He won his first trophy with the club on 21 May, when they were crowned league champions and managed to score his first league goal in a defeat of [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/gol-i-asistencija-dedica-za-titulu-prvaka-novac-od-dresa-ide-za-krajinu|title=Gol i asistencija Dedića za titulu prvaka, novac od dresa ide za Krajinu|website=n1info.ba|date=21 May 2023|access-date=23 May 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In February 2025, he was loaned to French outfit [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/amar-dedic-i-zvanicno-potpisao-za-marseille/3411855|title=Amar Dedić i zvanično potpisao za Marseille|website=fokus.ba|date=3 February 2025|access-date=3 February 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

===Benfica===
In June, Dedić was transferred to Portuguese side [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/benfica-predstavila-reprezentativca-bih-amar-dedic-novi-fudbaler-slavog-kluba|title=Benfica predstavila reprezentativca BiH: Amar Dedić novi fudbaler slavog kluba|website=n1info.ba|date=14 July 2025|access-date=17 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the club in the [[2025 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] match against [[Sporting CP]] on 31 July and managed to win his first trophy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/988638/amar-dedic-osvojio-prvi-trofej-s-benficom-medju-najboljima-na-terenu|title=Amar Dedić osvojio prvi trofej s Benficom: Među najboljima na terenu|website=avaz.ba|date=1 August 2025|access-date=1 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> Two weeks later, he made his league debut against [[C.F. Estrela da Amadora|Estrela]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/bh-reprezentativac-debitovao-u-ligi-amar-dedic-odigrao-90-minuta-protiv-estrele|title=Bh. reprezentativac debitovao u ligi: Amar Dedić odigrao 90 minuta protiv Estrele|website=sportske.ba|date=16 August 2025|access-date=17 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 31 August, he scored his first goal for Benfica in a victory over [[F.C. Alverca|Alverca]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/dedic-postigao-prvi-gol-za-benficu-majstorskim-driblingom-je-izbacio-dvojicu-igraca-iz-igre-i-pogodio/250831092|title=Dedić postigao prvi gol za Benficu, majstorskim driblingom je izbacio dvojicu igrača iz igre i pogodio|website=klix.ba|date=31 August 2025|access-date=1 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Dedić represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at all youth levels. He also served as a [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-17 football team|under-17 team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/349332-amar-dedic-cast-mi-je-uvijek-bila-da-igram-za-bih|title=Amar Dedić: Čast mi je uvijek bila da igram za BiH|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=28 January 2022|access-date=28 January 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In March 2022, he received his first senior call up, for [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] games against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] and [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/petev-objavio-spisak-zmajeva-za-utakmice-s-gruzijom-i-luksemburgom-dva-nova-imena/220311048|title=Petev objavio spisak Zmajeva za utakmice s Gruzijom i Luksemburgom, dva nova imena|website=klix.ba|date=11 March 2022|access-date=13 March 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the latter on 29 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/zmajevi-na-bilinom-polju-protiv-luksemburga-prekinuli-crni-niz/452054|title=Zmajevi na Bilinom polju protiv Luksemburga prekinuli crni niz|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 March 2022|access-date=1 April 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

On 23 March 2023, in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifier]] against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]], he scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/savrsen-start-kvalifikacija-za-ep-zmajevi-razbili-island-prvijenac-fenomenalnog-dedica|title=Savršen start kvalifikacija za EP: Zmajevi razbili Island, prvijenac fenomenalnog Dedića|website=scsport.ba|date=23 March 2023|access-date=24 March 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Dedić was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Dedić's father was born in [[Orahovica Donja]] near [[Gračanica, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Gračanica]], and his mother is from Lišnja near [[Prnjavor, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Prnjavor]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Amar Dedić nije zaboravio svoje porijeklo, posjetio je školu fudbala u Donjoj Orahovici |url=https://reprezentacija.ba/378040-amar-dedic-nije-zaboravio-svoje-porijeklo-posjetio-je-skolu-fudbala-u-donjoj-orahovici |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=Reprezentacija.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-24 |title=Ko je Amar Dedić, novi junak Zmajeva? |url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/ko-je-amar-dedic-novi-junak-zmajeva/ |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=N1 info |language=bs-BA}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Ermedin Demirović]], [[Tarik Muharemović]] and [[Dženis Burnić]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Sarajevo]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/zmajevi-snimljeni-na-dzumi-dedic-demirovic-muharemovic-i-burnic-bili-u-dzamiji-u-sarajevu/639157|title=Zmajevi snimljeni na džumi: Dedić, Demirović, Muharemović i Burnić bili u džamiji u Sarajevu|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

